 Job Description
 As a member of one of our Technology teams, you will contribute to building solutions that use natural language processing, cognitive computing, and artificial intelligence applications or the frameworks and infrastructure that support them.
 The Senior Systems Administrator is responsible for designing, planning, deploying, supporting and administering systems. The Senior System Administrator is also responsible for the implementation of appropriate tools to manage the Company's multi-site, 24x7 infrastructure.
 
Members of the Technical Operations team are the engine that drives Interactions. We are integral to the speed and stability of the Interactions locomotive. Not only will you support a 7x24x365 production environment, you will play with cutting-edge technologies, work on high-value projects and have a real opportunity to influence the direction of a highly successful company.
 
Interactions Technical Operations is a high-functioning, hard-driving and fun-loving group of professionals that define what it means to be a TEAM. Supporting data centers in the U.S. and Europe, weâ€™re looking to add another member to our ranks and need someone who is intelligent, curious, driven and loves challenges and gets bored easily. You will be made better by the people you work with and you must understand that our degree of success is directly proportional to our strength as a team.
 
 Essential Job Functions* : 
Maintain up to date, accurate documentation of all system configurations in company repositories.
 
Propose, develop and implement processes, policies and procedures related to the management of the company's infrastructure, including reliability, scalability, and security.
 
Manage and monitor infrastructure hardware and software, 3rd party software, server performance, space utilization, support, backups and disaster recovery.
 
Deploy system hardware, software and maintain patches and updates.
 
Actively participate in strategic technology planning and budget planning processes.
 
Research, evaluate and recommend solutions to improve and scale our service delivery infrastructure.
 
Participate in On-Call rotation requiring incident ownership from start to finish.
 
